        public java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> getBestActions(java.util.List<java.lang.String> boundNames,
                                                        java.util.List<java.lang.Boolean> useUbList,
                                                        boolean aggregate)
        Constructs a list of best actions according to the current bounds
        Parameters:
        boundNames - The name of the bounds to take into account
        useUb - Whether to use the lower or the upper bound for the corresponding bound
        aggregate - if true then all optimal actions for all boundNames are returned. If false then we assume a decreasing order of priority and use lower priority bounds to tie break a la nested VI
